<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>PR queen Roxy Jacenko showed herself undergoing a complete hair transformation on Tuesday. </p>

<p>And it appears the 40-year-old is over the moon with her new blunted bob. </p>

<p>On Wednesday, the entrepreneurial powerhouse Roxy looked high-glam as she posed in the mirror, with one side of her bob tucked behind her ear.</p>

<p>Tressed to impress! PR dynamo Roxy Jacenko showcased her short hair transformation on Wednesday, ahead of her return to screens in SAS Australia </p>

<p>'Oh hey,' Roxy wrote alongside her fresh new look. </p>

<p>In the image, Roxy let her blonde tresses fall to the front of her face. </p>

<p>The stunning blonde kept things simple on the day, wearing a plain white Under Armour T-shirt. </p>

<p>The Sweaty Betty PR founder wore a glossy makeup look which she paired with dark eye makeup and a matte lipstick. </p>

<p>Who's that girl? Roxy Jacenko shocked her fans on Tuesday by dramatically cutting her hair into a bob</p>

<p>Roxy's SAS Australia co-star Ali Oetjen commented on the photograph: 'HAAAWTT! Wow!!'     </p>

<p>On Tuesday, Roxy uploaded a video of herself undergoing the major transformation while sitting in the chair of celebrity hairdresser and hair stylist, Travis Balcke.</p>

<p>'It was time,' she captioned her Instagram post. </p>

<p>Her usual look: The PR powerhouse has long been known for her long blonde bouncy tresses</p>

<p>It is not the first time the blonde beauty has looked dramatically different.</p>

<p>The mother-of-two sported a noticeably smoother visage and a plumper-looking pout earlier this month in a promotional photo for her online marketing classes. </p>

<p>Roxy will next be seen on SAS Australia. She and convicted drug smuggler Schapelle Corby reportedly 'walked' from the new series. </p>

<p>According to The Daily Telegraph in August, the two stars are understood to have left just days into filming.</p>

<p>The report goes on to say that Roxy departed the series due to a 'lack of comforts' while Schapelle struggled with the 'fitness' aspect of the gruelling new reality series.</p>

<p>Bye: Roxy Jacenko, 40, and Schapelle Corby, 43, are the first to 'leave' the new Channel Seven reality series SAS Australia, according to The Daily Telegraph last month</p>
